        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 19 at 7:31PM CDT until April 19 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>SVRMAF

The National Weather Service in Midland has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Upton County in western Texas...

* Until 800 PM CDT.

* At 730 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near McCamey,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Law enforcement reported golf ball size hail in McCamey
at 722 PM CDT.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
McCamey and Upton County Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
